Definition.WordDefinition: Photo \Pho"to\, n.; pl. {Photos}. A contraction of {Photograph}. [Colloq.] [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Photo- \Pho"to-\ A combining form from Gr. fw^s, fwto`s, light; as, photography, phototype, photometer. [1913 Webster]
photo n : a picture of a person or scene in the form of a print or transparent slide; recorded by a camera on light-sensitive material [syn: {photograph}, {exposure}, {pic}]
